OL,7,FAround 10 patches of grass were found
OL,8,Fto have been lifted and put back, in a
OL,9,Fso-called nighthawking incident.
OL,11,FNighthawking is the theft of
OL,12,Farchaeological artefacts from
OL,13,Fprotected archaeological sites and
OL,14,Fareas, and is illegal. People found
OL,15,Fguilty of offences under the Ancient
OL,16,FMonuments and Archaeological Areas Act
OL,17,F1979 can receive a substantial fine
OL,18,Fand be sent to prison.
